annotation.TEXT: Oh, it takes me straight to that level between worlds 1 and 2. And, the level above that has disappeared and been replaced with a bridge segment (which isn't a level I can enter). I'm guessing that finishing worlds 4, 5, and 6 will complete the bridge and allow me to enter the Bowser head.
Okay, now that I got my flower back, I'm just gonna take a peek at where this star leads...
Ooh, interesting music, and is this the title demo level? I believe it is!
I should've been able to avoid the fireball there, but Wendy is defeated all the same.
And now for that Yoshi coin...
Of course, without Yoshi, I'm trapped in world 6 for now, but before I even consider entering 6-2, I'm going to go back to 6-1 briefly...
I could probably cape spin this guy easily, but... fireballs, yeah.
Obviously, this is a conveyor belt.
Fire Bros... Am I going to encounter the whole Hammer Bro family in this castle?
Yep! And now I get to tear things apart! Oh, yeah!!!
There's a Yoshi coin in that pit. Well, before I dive down there, I want to check out what's to the right first...
Well, I'll just leave this overworld music playing for a little while here. And thanks go to JessePrower for letting me know what this music is! It's Vile's Stage from Mega Man X3.
Whoa, holy crap! Did you see that? That 1-up tried to kill me, man! Good thing I'm caped!
Seems like somewhat unfair level design if you ask me. (Of course, the previous level had that badly placed hidden 1-up as well. Maybe this whole world is less fair!)
Nuts! That was a bad misplay on my part.
Nuts. It's Wendy, which means the flower isn't of any use. Oh, well...
Okay, I think I'm good for now.
I hope there's a cape in one of those...
Oh, this is so Oil Drum Alley from DKC, complete with the music and the flaming barrels (sort of)!
Ha, ha!
Now, unfortunately, I made a mistake here. The next most popular vote was world 5 with 3 votes, and world 6 got 1 vote. (Oddly, I didn't see any votes for world 4...)
Okay, now for the castle.
Yeah, you can't normal jump on them at all. That's what I thought. At least it was a fairly safe test, since I can just get my power up back easily.
To be continued...
You never know where a secret may be...
Yep, these blocks are indeed ON/OFF controlled, so I would've died if I had just hopped in after that Yoshi coin right away!
(Hmm... There's no Maverick that's gonna ambush me, is there? No? Good.) Ha, ha!
I'll just briefly show these messages again, in case anyone forgot what they said. (Pause the video if you need more time to read them.)
I see an opening up there! You know what that means!
That's a 7-life combo right there, but wait, there's more!
Gah! Stupid surprise diagonal bullets! Now I'm without Yoshi again, probably for most of the world, just like last time!
Actually, that wasn't that bad, although I guess my cape helped a bit there.
Oh, hi, Yoshi!
Now with the serious votes, both the castle and Yoshi's House got 5 votes, but Yoshi's House was the first pick more times, so I'm starting with that.
There's those silver munchers again. I don't trust them, so I'm going to avoid them entirely.
Argh!!! I was too busy laughing at that other guy...
KA-BOOOOOOM!!!
I see you over there, Maverick Thwomp, eyeing me...
Finish! I'm honestly glad that level's over. So many things could've gone terribly wrong, but didn't!
And there's a mushroom in this bush, but that seems to be about it...
Be careful. I can't expect a miracle every time I screw up!
First, the silly votes: 2 votes for me to redo 3-1, 1 vote for over 9000-1, and 1 vote for me to use Yoshi to terrorize the world from above!
Well, let's start 6-1.

However, while I was actually playing, I thought that world 6 was the one with 3 votes for some reason, and I didn't realize my mistake until much later. Sorry, I'll try not to screw up like that again in the future...
Can't cape spin these guys. Hey, you know what? There's a spare feather in that block to the left, so...
So, I guess this is an industrial world of some sort. Well, let's begin 6-2.
This appears to be like a Top Secret Area style level, but I wonder if there's anything hidden offscreen?
Thank you! Ah, there is something up here. There's a blue block that switches back and forth on its own, but it's not like I need it...
Okay, and this is where I flew up to that bonus room initially.
Something something, something, something. ...Something.
Wow, that was messy! I took three hits in a row there, but I still managed to make it to the goal alive!
Also, coincidentally, this level between worlds 1 and 2 was the next most popular, with 4 votes, so let's check it out!
Purple buzzies? Well, I bounce off of them with a spin jump... Are they really spinies?
A regular mushroom? No thanks.
A bunch of somethings.
I guess that's a handy way to quickly get a Yoshi over here if you need to.
I think a spare feather will be more useful than a flower here.
Oh, yeah. These Ball 'N Chains can't hurt Yoshi. Gotta remember that.
Yep, that's a 4-life combo! I'm sure I could've gone much further, but I don't want to waste too much time, and the lives are meaningless anyway.
And neither can these saws, so I can tap dance on them all I want without fear!
Thanks go to Glitch4Mr for letting me know what this cool music is! It's Magnet Man's Stage from the Game Boy Mega Man 2.
Argh, not again!
And that unlocks 6-3, which is a red level, and which I'll be exploring next time!
Does the P-switch affect the cyan blocks?
Whoa, geez! I really should've died there, but my life was saved by a glitchy block! I'm not gonna complain about this bug!
Nice! Now let's try not to be an idiot anymore.
Yeah, I figured there was hidden stuff here!
This is the only new level that I can access right now, so there's no point in voting... Although, I suppose you guys can vote on the levels unlocked by 6-3's normal exit and secret exit afterwards.
Extra cape. Might be handy.
WHOA! If these blocks are ON/OFF controlled, then it would've been deadly for me to drop down here without changing the switch, and I would've had no way of knowing that!
Oh, god, no! Well, let's see how well I do here...
This looks like a dark version of part of Chocolate Island 2...
Ten lives total in one bonus room. Not bad at all! (Except I already had max lives, but whatever.)
Huh? A warp star? Hmm... I'm curious... But, first, I wanna go back to this Yoshi's House for a moment...
Hmm... I wonder why the right "drum" isn't burning there...
Hello, and welcome back to Super SIG World 21! Let's take a look at the voting results this time...
I doubt it.
An ON/OFF switch... I wonder which way it should be set. Well, I'll turn it off I guess. I mean, why even come over here if I'm not going to switch it?
There's nothing up there (I don't think), and going to the right just exits the level.
Which way should this one be set? I will guess OFF.
That pipe probably leads to the boss, so I'm going to switch to the flower and hope for a quick kill.
A bonus room of some sort?
Okay, and now that I've hit a switch, I can enter one of these doors... But not while on Yoshi I'm afraid. Sorry, but... Bye, Yoshi!
Hey, I was right! That spring would've gone down the hole if it was set to ON.
It even has red parakoopas. I wonder if I can get a combo going here...
Now what did that bonus room skip over?
D'oh!
D'oh! Hey, stupid koopa up there! Open the door so I can take off!
Luigifan22222's translation: "-Advantageous Information- There seems to be a switch in the basement of some stages something or other. Should you check it if interested?"
Luigifan22222's translation: "I beat progress, one of The Four Heavenly Kings, Wendy in a slightly weird forest. She was not pretty at all as ever."
